notesStmt.note: Title for manuscript from title page of first work (f. 1r).

msContents.summary: Collection of 18th-century Latin and Italian verse. 2 long works concern the War of Polish Succession (f. 1r-19v, 26r) and the War of Austrian Succession (f. 30r-104v), with a short poem possibly on the 1740 funeral of Friedrich Wilhelm of Prussia (f. 20r-24r) and an epistle in verse to an aristocratic patron, Donato de Silva, written on a larger bifolium, tipped in and folded (f. 27r-28v).
